"},{"content":"Transfer into a sealable container and allow to cool to room temperature before placing in the refrigerator until required."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Pistachio and Oat Granola"},{"content":"Preheat oven to 150°C. Line a deep-sided roasting tray (32 x 23 cm) with baking paper and set aside."},{"content":"Place sugar, maple syrup, olive oil and salt in mixing bowl then heat <b>3 min\/80°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add pistachios, oats and almonds then mix <b>6 sec\/speed 4<b>, or until mixture is combined."},{"content":"Spread mixture onto prepared roasting tray and bake for 8 minutes (150°C). Remove tray from oven, stir mixture and bake for a further 6-8 minutes (150°C), or until granola is dry and lightly golden. Set aside to cool (approx. 15 minutes)."},{"content":"Once cooled, transfer granola into a sealable container to store until ready to use."},{"content":"Lightly toast the fruit bread, then spread each slice with goat's cheese. Top with cooled fruit compôte, then sprinkle with a little granola and a drizzle of honey, just before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Serve leftover pistachio and oat granola on top of natural yoghurt and fresh fruit or as a base for homemade granola bars.","Try using a variety of seasonal fruits in the compôte.","<strong>Rhubarb topping:<\/strong> Place 500 g water into mixing bowl. Line Varoma dish with a piece of wet and well-wrung baking paper. Place Varoma into position and weigh 350 g rhubarb, cut into lengths (5 cm) on top of the baking paper. Drizzle with 20 g honey; ½ orange, zest only, no white pith; 2-3 cm piece ginger, peeled and grated; and 1-2 pinches cinnamon. Secure Varoma lid and steam <strong>13-15 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/strong>, or until rhubarb is tender. Set rhubarb aside in a bowl, drizzle with an additional 20 g honey and allow to cool. Use the rhubarb topping in place of the mixed fruit compôte."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","50m","4 portions"]}